@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Company Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>At EMS, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users' personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal data when you use our services or interact with our website.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect personal information from you when you register on our website, subscribe to our newsletter, fill out a form, or interact with our services. The information we may collect includes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Full name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>Address</li>
        <li>Date of birth</li>
        <li>Gender</li>
        <li>Other relevant details for providing our services</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We use this information to provide and improve our services, communicate with you, and ensure the security of our systems.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We may use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and personalize our services</li>
        <li>Process and manage your account</li>
        <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
        <li>Send you newsletters, marketing communications, and promotional offers (with your consent)</li>
        <li>Improve our website and services</li>
        <li>Protect the security and integrity of our systems</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website and delivering our services. These third parties are obligated to keep your information confidential and are prohibited from using your personal data for any other purpose.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Retention of Your Information</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy and as required by applicable laws. Once your information is no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize it.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Security of Your Information</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the security of your personal information and prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no data transmission or storage system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. If you have any concerns about the security of your information, please contact us.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to access, update, correct, and delete your personal information. You may also have the right to restrict or object to certain processing activities. If you wish to exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details provided below.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated policy on our website. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Data Security and Confidentiality</h2>
    <p>We prioritize the security and confidentiality of your data. We implement industry-standard measures to protect your personal and sensitive information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or alteration. Our employees are trained on data security best practices and are bound by strict confidentiality agreements.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Data Usage and Consent</h2>
    <p>We only collect and process your personal information for legitimate purposes related to providing our services. We do not share your data with third parties without your explicit consent, except as required by law. By using our system, you consent to the collection, processing, and storage of your data as outlined in this policy.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>User Responsibilities</h2>
    <p>As a user of our Employee Management System, you are responsible for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Maintaining the confidentiality of your login credentials and not sharing them with unauthorized individuals.</li>
        <li>Ensuring the accuracy and completeness of the information you provide.</li>
        <li>Complying with applicable laws, regulations, and company policies when using the system.</li>
        <li>Respecting the privacy and rights of other users.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Any misuse, unauthorized access, or violation of these responsibilities may result in disciplinary action, including termination of access to the system.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Data Access and Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to access, modify, and delete your personal information stored in our Employee Management System. If you wish to exercise these rights or have any concerns regarding your data, please contact our support team.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Acceptable Use Policy</h2>
    <p>Our Employee Management System should be used for work-related purposes only. Any unauthorized use, including but not limited to accessing or sharing inappropriate, offensive, or confidential information, is strictly prohibited. Violation of this policy may result in disciplinary action.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain user data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected and to comply with legal obligations. When data is no longer required, we securely delete or anonymize it. You have the right to request the deletion of your data, subject to applicable laws and regulations.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Password Policy</h2>
    <p>To ensure the security of your account, we enforce the following password policy:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Use a combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters.</li>
        <li>Choose a password that is at least 8 characters long.</li>
        <li>Avoid using easily guessable information, such as your name or birthdate, as part of your password.</li>
        <li>Do not reuse passwords across different platforms or accounts.</li>
        <li>Regularly update your password and avoid sharing it with others.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We recommend that you follow these guidelines to protect your account from unauthorized access.</p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Email: admin@EMS.com</li>
        <li>Phone: [+123456789]</li>
    </ul>
</div>
